The paper proposes the use of Deep Reinforcement Learning for developing adaptive learning-based solutions for autonomous driving systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the planning and control of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper involves the use of sensor observations, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with multi-agent settings, which suggests that it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
